The paper discusses a security vulnerability in biometric template protection schemes, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack framework proposed in the paper involves the use of genetic algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The paper also introduces new metrics to measure the effectiveness of the attack, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
